Virtus – Virtus Partners




















 


















Login
























Who we are





Virtus has been delivering value to the alternative investment industry since 2005































Virtus Partners provides solutions for asset managers, banks, hedge funds, and investors  to better manage a wide variety of alternative investment strategies. We understand that different clients may require different solutions, so our services are flexible and tailored to fit your specific requirements.  We work with a range of clientele, from fixed-income managers to hedge fund software providers.
Headquartered in Houston, Texas the company has grown from a four person firm in 2005 to a global leader in our industry. We have leveraged our bank debt expertise to expand beyond the CLO market and offer a comprehensive set of solutions covering the broader alternative investment landscape. Today, over 300 employees in five offices in the United States and Europe administer over $350 billion dollars worth of assets for over 100 global financial institutions.
 
Virtus Timeline
 
 
Clients
Virtus has a large and growing client base consisting of many of the world’s largest banks, hedge funds and asset managers.  The deals that Virtus administers on behalf of these clients  typically have lives of 5-7 years and are recurring in nature.  Virtus is administering over 750 individual portfolios for 100 different managers.  Over half of our clients have multiple deals with Virtus and no client represents more than 20% of our portfolio.

Leadership
Virtus Partners was started in 2005 by its four partners who all remain actively engaged with the business on a daily basis. The name Virtus comes from ancient Rome and embodies concepts of excellence, character, and courage.  It took courage for the four founding partners to step out on their own and start a new firm that would fulfill their vision of an independent company that combined cutting edge technology and exceptional customer service would better serve their customers in the structured credit industry. Partners represents the founding partners, but also the partnership between the founders and their employees and again with the firm’s clients.









Joe Elston
Partner

Joe Elston
Partner
Joe Elston is a Co-Founder and Partner for Virtus Partners, LLC. His primary focus includes managing Virtus’ new business, sales, and marketing efforts. Joe has over twenty years of experience in the financial services industry with assignments ranging from loan origination to trust services. Prior to founding Virtus, Joe was lead sales and deal manager at the JPMorgan CDO Trust group and a US Navy Surface Warfare Officer.
 
Joe earned a BBA degree in Finance from Southern Methodist University and a MA and PHD from the University of Nebraska-Lincoln in Political Science with an emphasis in Economics.







Kelly Faykus
Managing Partner

Kelly Faykus
Managing Partner
Kelly Faykus is a Co-Founder and Managing Partner for Virtus Partners. Kelly oversees all aspects of Virtus’ daily operations and strategic relationships.  He has over twenty years in the financial services industry in varying capacities from loan origination to trust services. Prior to founding Virtus, Kelly was the head of Sales and New Business for the JPMorgan CDO group.
 
Kelly earned a BS degree in Finance from Texas A&M and an MBA from University of Michigan in Ann Arbor.







Mirna Herr
Partner

Mirna Herr
Partner
Mirna Herr is a Co-Founder and Partner for Virtus Partners, LLC. She is responsible for all aspects of the firm’s operational areas, management of client relationships, and services. Mirna brings over 15 years of experience in the financial services industry. Prior to founding Virtus, Mirna held management positions at JPMorgan playing active roles in key client relationships and serving critical roles for process improvement and implementation.
 
Mirna earned a BS degree in Accounting from the University of Houston-Clear Lake.







Robert Tomicic
Partner

Robert Tomicic
Partner
Robert Tomicic is a Co-Founder and Partner for Virtus Partners, LLC. His primary focus includes managing Virtus’ product development, strategy and analytics. Robert has over twenty years of experience in the financial services and management consulting industries.
 
Prior to founding Virtus, Robert was the Global CDO Product Manager for the JPMorgan CDO Trust group. While working within JP Morgan’s Trust Group he had positions as Global Manager of Analytics and CDO Administration Manager. Prior to JPMorgan, Robert was an IT consultant with Ernst & Young LLP.
 
Robert earned BA degree in Economics from the University of Western Ontario, a BA degree in Commerce from the University of Windsor Ontario and an MBA in Finance from Texas Tech University.













